CITATION: 1977 AIR 2319 1978 SCR (1) 547 1977 SCC (4) 309 
ACT:
 Limitation Act, 1963, Sections 5, 12, 12(2), Explanation to sec. 12-Whether the time between the date of the judgment and the date of the preparation of the decree is to be excluded for the purposes of limitation if application for certified copy is made after the decree was prepared-If there was a legal impediment against preparation of the decree on account of certain directions in the judgement whether position would be different-When a litigant requests his advocate to take all steps without any laches and if there is indifference or negligence on the part of the advocate, whether delay should be condoned.
 
